}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/syndication/thread/1.0";a:1:{s:5:"total";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2:"14";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";a:8:{s:2:"id";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-7407232695424203415.post-6077622775788877147";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:9:"published";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"2010-04-14T15:43:00.000-07:00";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"updated";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"2010-04-14T15:48:52.207-07:00";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:2:{s:6:"scheme";s:31:"http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#";s:4:"term";s:8:"blogging";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:42:"Hoping This Blog is Bigger Than "ME ME ME"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:4:"type";s:4:"text";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3598:"<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_CqvhCR9-IRg/S8ZFlaBXtRI/AAAAAAAAACg/yekgkMS9W-k/s1600/DSC_9971.JPG"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 400px; height: 266px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_CqvhCR9-IRg/S8ZFlaBXtRI/AAAAAAAAACg/yekgkMS9W-k/s400/DSC_9971.JPG" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5460128107175851282" /></a><br /><p class="MsoNormal">In undergrad and grad school, I often needed to write an Ars Poetica (justification of writing poetry, written in verse) at the end of each semester’s writing workshop.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>It was a useful exercise in many ways, as it required me to really examine what mattered to me in the work I was doing.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>I think I want to do the same thing, briefly, for this blog (an Ars Blogica?).<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>Last night, somebody important to me made a disparaging comment about my desire to keep this blog.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>“Are you looking for people to feel sorry for you?<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>Isn’t this just ‘Waah, look what I’ve been through?’” person X asked.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>The answer is no.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>I don’t want anyone to feel sorry for me.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>I would prefer that people thought I was tough.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">   </span>But the question made me want to lay out some of my reasons for doing this and what I hope this “project” can yield.</p>  <p class="MsoNormal">It’s no secret that the nature of the blogosphere is narcissistic.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>Well, duh.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>Every act of writing is, to a certain extent, narcissistic.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>One of my favorite poetry teachers once told me that when we write poems, we are asking the reader to fall in love with us.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>And I believe that, beloved reader.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>But what about this blog? I hope that what I write here is about more than just me.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>When I write about my experiences, I am trying to create meaning from them.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>What use is pain if you can’t find meaning in it, learn something from it (even if it is something you’d prefer not to learn, like how selfish you can be), or find some humor buried somewhere in it?<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>That is what I aim to do.  Try to make sense of my experience and make it into something meaningful to more than just me. <span style="mso-spacerun:yes"></span></p>  <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-spacerun:yes"> </span>I’ve only been doing this for nine days, but I’ve been enjoying it.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>It guarantees that I write every day, it gives me a place to formulate my thoughts on important topics through writing, and, most importantly, it has introduced me to people who have had similar experiences or know more than I do.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>That feels like enough.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>I hope it is.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span></p><div class="blogger-post-footer"><img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/7407232695424203415-6077622775788877147?l=bigbadblondebahu.blogspot.com' alt='' /></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:4:"type";s:4:"html";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:4:{s:3:"rel";s:7:"replies";s:4:"type";s:20:"application/atom+xml";s:4:"href";s:79:"http://bigbadblondebahu.blogspot.com/feeds/6077622775788877147/comments/default";s:5:"title";s:13:"Post Comments";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:4:{s:3:"rel";s:7:"replies";s:4:"type";s:9:"text/html";s:4:"href";s:100:"http://bigbadblondebahu.blogspot.com/2010/04/hoping-this-blog-is-bigger-than-me-me.html#comment-form";s:5:"title";s:10:"6 Comments";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"rel";s:4:"edit";s:4:"type";s:20:"application/atom+xml";s:4:"h