il.com";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://schemas.google.com/g/2005";a:1:{s:16:"extendedProperty";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:2:{s:4:"name";s:16:"OpenSocialUserId";s:5:"value";s:20:"12345428661160738637";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/syndication/thread/1.0";a:1:{s:5:"total";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"8";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:11;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";a:7:{s:2:"id";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-7407232695424203415.post-2277083166434765216";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:9:"published";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"2010-04-11T18:25:00.000-07:00";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"updated";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"2010-04-11T18:36:05.827-07:00";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"Conversation Lost in Translation:  Worship the Tree Like It's Your Husband";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:4:"type";s:4:"text";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2636:"<a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_CqvhCR9-IRg/S8J3CMpXJSI/AAAAAAAAACY/NixUIKuP3E4/s1600/DSC_9980.JPG"><img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 400px; height: 266px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_CqvhCR9-IRg/S8J3CMpXJSI/AAAAAAAAACY/NixUIKuP3E4/s400/DSC_9980.JPG" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5459056577964614946" /></a><br />This might be the first in a series of short posts.  <div><br /></div><div><p class="MsoNormal">The scene:<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>an unpaved road in Maharashtra.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>A herd of goats has just walked by.</p>  <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-tab-count:1">                </span>“So, when the bangles are nailed to the tree like this, the wife can then worship the tree as the husband.”</p>  <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-tab-count:1">                </span>“What?<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>I think I missed something.”</p>  <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-tab-count:1">                </span>“Oh, you see that someone has nailed these green bangles to the tree?”<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>My husband’s cousin pointed to them as though perhaps I had not seen them.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span>Someone had, indeed, nailed some green glass bangles to a ficus tree.  I knew that married Maharashtrian women wear green bangles, and that a tree is a perfectly acceptable temple, but I wasn't sure where she was going with this.</p>  <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-tab-count:1">                </span>“And they have done this as some kind of offering to a specific god?” I asked, hoping she could clarify the point.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">  </span></p>  <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-tab-count:1">                </span>“By keeping the bangles on the tree, she can worship it as her husband.”</p><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">  </span>I nodded as though I knew what she meant and kept walking, but I couldn't help but wonder.  Did she just lack the vocabulary to express herself, or did she, a woman only a few years older than me, think that women should "worship" their husbands?  Later, I tried asking my husband what his cousin was talking about.  He had no idea either.  </p></div><div class="blogger-post-footer"><img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/7407232695424203415-2277083166434765216?l=bigbadblondebahu.blogspot.com' alt='' /></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:4:"type";s:4:"html";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:4:{s:3:"rel";s:7:"replies";s:4:"type";s:20:"application/atom+xml";s:4:"href";s:79:"http://bigbadblondebahu.blogspot.com/feeds/2277083166434765216/comments/default";s:5:"title";s:13:"Post Comments";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:4:{s:3:"rel";s:7:"replies";s:4:"type";s:9:"text/html";s:4:"href";s:95:"http://bigbadblondebahu.blogspot.com/2010/04/conversation-lost-in-translation.html#comment-form";s:5:"title";s:10:"2 Comments";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"rel";s:4:"edit";s:4:"type";s:20:"application/atom+xml";s:4:"href";s:82:"http://www.blogger.com/feeds/7407232695424203415/posts/default/2277083166434765216";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"rel";s:4:"self";s:4:"type";s:20:"application/atom+xml";s:4:"href";s:82:"http://www.blogger.com/feeds/7407232695424203415/posts/default/2277083166434765216";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:4:{s:3:"rel";s:9:"alternate";s:4:"type";s:9:"text/html";s:4:"href";s:82:"http://bigbadblondebahu.blogspot.com/2010/04/conversation-lost-in-translation.html";s:5:"title";s:74:"Conversation Lost in Translation:  Worship the Tree Like It's Your Husband";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"